# Component Authoring

Docs: [design-system.md](../../apps/web/docs/design-system.md) · [components.md](../../apps/web/docs/components.md)

## Every new component requires

- A co-located `<name>.stories.tsx` (CSF3: `Meta<typeof Component>`, named `StoryObj` exports)
- A co-located `<name>.test.tsx` (Vitest + Testing Library)

## Server vs client

- Client component → `<name>.client.tsx` + `'use client'` as the first line
- Server component → `<name>.tsx`, no directive

## UI primitives (`components/ui/`)

Follow the CVA pattern:

```
<primitive>/
├── index.ts                  barrel export
├── <primitive>.variants.ts   all cva() definitions — Tailwind classes live here only
├── <primitive>.types.ts      optional; add when the component exports non-trivial prop types for consumers
├── <primitive>.tsx           component — no raw class strings
└── <primitive>.stories.tsx
```

## Accessibility

Components must not introduce WCAG 2.2 AA violations. Colour contrast, focus management, keyboard operability, and landmark structure are component-level concerns — not just test-time checks.

## Tailwind / design tokens

- Prefer named CVA variants over long inline class strings. When a combination of classes represents a reusable visual concept, it belongs in `*.variants.ts`, not the template.
- All Tailwind class strings belong in `*.variants.ts`; compose in the component via `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`
- Never hardcode color values or font sizes — use CSS token classes (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-h2`, etc.)
- Design tokens are the SSoT: `styles/tokens/colors.css`, `typography.css`, `base.css`
